    {
        "content": "<p>Agree we need to fix the color in the popover. Also:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The left sidebar topic row placement looks a bit misaligned vertically.</li>\n<li>The notification settings @ in the popover should just be an <code>@</code> character.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>My current feeling from these screenshots is that just using <code>@</code> characters in our fonts everywhere might look better. In particular, the <code>@all</code> in notification settings doesn't look great, I think because it's a style mismatch between the icon and font designs.</p>",
        "id": 1429713,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1662145349
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>here regular text symbol is ok <a href=\"/user_uploads/2/40/ptG3PNTz6JxYuk97J5tk9iK_/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/40/ptG3PNTz6JxYuk97J5tk9iK_/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/40/ptG3PNTz6JxYuk97J5tk9iK_/image.png\"></a></div>",
